questions.prompt: Due in large part to a show he hosted from 1952 to 1989, TV pioneer Dick Clark was often dubbed (especially in tributes after his death in 2012) as "America's oldest" what?

These four properties define what geometric figure (i.e., any shape that has these four properties is this geometric figure, by definition)?

1) A sport, 2) A financial measure of active ROI (but misspelled), 3) A Shakespeare character, 4) A New York Judge. These descriptions of code words in the NATO phonetic alphabet, when converted to the letters they represent, spell the name of what city?
